###############################################################################
# .cursorrules — TLDR (single-service TypeScript Slack AI App)
###############################################################################

<language>
1. Primary language is TypeScript (Node 20+); the runtime is AWS Lambda.
2. Infrastructure is Terraform (`terraform/`), deployed via `terraform apply` (CI runs it on merge to main).

<code_style>
3. Strict TypeScript everywhere. No `any` unless explicitly justified.
4. Use `KnownBlock` / `Button` from `@slack/types` for Block Kit.
5. Match existing import style: group third-party then local; never glob-import.
6. Prefer Bolt's `WebClient` (`@slack/web-api`) over hand-rolled HTTP. Use
   `client.apiCall()` only for endpoints not yet exposed in the typed surface.

<linting>
7. Must pass `npm run lint` (ESLint with strict TS rules).
8. Tests live under `bolt-ts/tests/` and mirror `bolt-ts/src/`; one test file per
   module. TDD is the default.

<error_handling>
9. Surface Anthropic / Slack errors via the canonical failure message and clean
   up partial Slack streaming messages — see `worker/streaming.ts`.
10. Never log secrets (Slack bot token, Anthropic API key) or full prompt bodies.

<architecture>
11. The repo is a single-service Slack app. Long-running summarisation happens
    inline within the Bolt `userMessage` handler — there is no SQS, no second
    Lambda. Anyone proposing to reintroduce a queue must justify it.
12. Bolt internally ACKs Slack events; we rely on Bolt's built-in retry
    deduplication via `event_id` for idempotency.

<dependencies>
13. Default to the existing dependency set: `@anthropic-ai/sdk`, `@slack/bolt`,
    `@slack/web-api`, `@slack/types`, `@aws-sdk/client-ssm`, `uuid`. Add new
    dependencies only when standard library + existing deps can't reasonably
    solve the problem.

<tests_docs>
14. Add Jest tests for new functionality.
15. Update `CLAUDE.md` and `README.md` when behaviour shifts in a user-visible
    way.

# Pre-commit
- Run `just qa` before committing. CI runs the same gate.
